doc.after: Aircraft equipped with contra rotating propellers also referred to as CRP 1 coaxial contra rotating propellers or high speed propellers apply the maximum power of usually a single piston or turboprop engine to drive two coaxial propellers in contra rotation rotation about the same axis in opposite directions Two propellers are arranged one behind the other and power is transferred from the engine via a planetary gear or spur gear transmission Contra rotating propellers should not be confused with counter rotating propellers airscrews on separate shafts turning opposite directions
